com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Interface ArrayEntry


  • public interface ArrayEntry
    UPA entry for Array that can house only simple primitive types such as Int, Real, or Date.
    See Also:
    Array

    • Method Detail

      • clear

        void clear()
        Clears ArrayEntry object. Useful for object reuse during encoding. While decoding, ArrayEntry object can be reused without using clear().

      • encode

        int encode(EncodeIterator iter)
        Encodes an ArrayEntry from pre-encoded data. This method expects the same EncodeIterator that was used with Array.encodeInit(EncodeIterator). Typical use:
        1. Call Array.encodeInit()
        2. Call ArrayEntry.encode() for each entry using the same buffer
        3. Call Array.encodeComplete()
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator

      • encode

        int encode(EncodeIterator iter,
           Buffer data)
        Perform array item encoding of a Buffer.
        The length of the buffer should be the same as the itemLength of the array; only the shorter of the two will be copied. The entry is encoded as blank when the data is null or when the data length is 0.
        Parameters:
        iter - The encoder iterator.
        data - The Buffer.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes
        See Also:
        EncodeIterator, Buffer

      • encodedData

        Buffer encodedData()
        Raw data contents of the array entry. Set by decode() method during decode or set with encoded content and used with the encode(iter) method.
